column24:
In this part you will be asked to find a single flickering object within a scene. Each time you will be presented with one scene. This scene will be static, except for one single object that will be appearing and disappearing. Your goal will be to detect this object as quickly and accurately as you can.

We will ask you to place your finger over the space bar, and once you have found the object press the space bar as quickly as possible.

For each scene, you will have up to 60 seconds to do so. After that you will be asked about the location of the object.


We will now continue with a short practice before starting the task.


Press the space bar to continue

In this part you will be asked to find a single flickering object within a scene. Each time you will be presented with one scene. This scene will be static, except for one single object that will be appearing and disappearing. Your goal will be to detect this object as quickly and accurately as you can.

We will ask you to place your finger over the space bar, and once you have found the object press the space bar as quickly as possible.

For each scene, you will have up to 60 seconds to do so. After that you will be asked about the location of the object.


We will now continue with a short practice before starting the task.


Press the space bar to continue

column24:
In this part you will be asked to find a single flickering object within a scene. Each time you will be presented with one scene. This scene will be static, except for one single object that will be appearing and disappearing. Your goal will be to detect this object as quickly and accurately as you can.

We will ask you to place your finger over the space bar, and once you have found the object press the space bar as quickly as possible.

For each scene, you will have up to 60 seconds to do so. After that you will be asked about the location of the object.


We will now continue with a short practice before starting the task.


Press the space bar to continue

In this part you will be asked to find a single flickering object within a scene. Each time you will be presented with one scene. This scene will be static, except for one single object that will be appearing and disappearing. Your goal will be to detect this object as quickly and accurately as you can.

We will ask you to place your finger over the space bar, and once you have found the object press the space bar as quickly as possible.

For each scene, you will have up to 60 seconds to do so. After that you will be asked about the location of the object.


We will now continue with a short practice before starting the task.


Press the space bar to continue

This scene will be static, except for one single object that will be appearing and disappearing. Your goal will be to detect this object as quickly and accurately as you can.

We will ask you to place your finger over the space bar, and once you have found the object press the space bar as quickly as possible.

column24:
In this part you will be asked to find a single flickering object within a scene. Each time you will be presented with one scene. This scene will be static, except for one single object that will be appearing and disappearing. Your goal will be to detect this object as quickly and accurately as you can.

We will ask you to place your finger over the space bar, and once you have found the object press the space bar as quickly as possible.

For each scene, you will have up to 60 seconds to do so. After that you will be asked about the location of the object.


We will now continue with a short practice before starting the task.


Press the space bar to continue

In this part you will be asked to find a single flickering object within a scene. Each time you will be presented with one scene. This scene will be static, except for one single object that will be appearing and disappearing. Your goal will be to detect this object as quickly and accurately as you can.

We will ask you to place your finger over the space bar, and once you have found the object press the space bar as quickly as possible.

For each scene, you will have up to 60 seconds to do so. After that you will be asked about the location of the object.


We will now continue with a short practice before starting the task.


Press the space bar to continue
